Agent of the Balance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/28/02 9:24:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=292.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Personal Attacks</span><hr size=1> No, I was comparing the speed of him being banned to the speed of Pee Wee Herman being thrown out of an adult movie theater :P<br>
<br>
Depends. What're you looking for? I'm helping open up this great, new one called AtG. We're always looking for play-testers. Roleplaying enforced, not quite classic fantasy. Tons of great features, too. We're making completely different mobs from what's been out. I.e. instead of that lioness always aggroing on you, there's a 1% chance that it will, that 1% chance being something like you coming too close to the cubs, disturbing her territory, or so forth.<br>
<br>
There's a bunch of great roleplaying ones out there. Armageddon is a good one. Lotsa people like it. It takes place in a Dark Sun-like world. Decent roleplaying, but no ANSI color, and it takes a moment to go between rooms, which I don't like.<br>
<br>
If you're looking for PK, try something using a Godwars codebase. I played on some MUD before that started everyone off at the max level, level 50, and just set them against each other. That was A LOT of fun. Lost the address of that.<br>
<br>
It all depends on what you're looking for. MUSHs are for hardcore roleplaying, honestly. As in, all you do is roleplay, no levelling up or anything. They're fun, to a point. If no one's around, it gets really boring. And they're mostly for Tabletop games, such as Shadowrun or D&amp;D. Use mudconnector.com to search, though. Great site right there. If you need any more advice on MUDs, feel free to ask. <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>
Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>
Agent of The Ring <BR>
